<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,402,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Variation.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[326,427,403,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Paratype</typeStatus>
, small male (OMNH-Ar-12430, 
<quantity box="[793,883,402,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" unit="mm" value="5.1">5.1 mm</quantity>
). 
<emphasis box="[902,1049,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Gnathopod 1</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1064,1131,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[194,1392,195,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-26@6.[181,1406,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Aora biarticulata sp. nov. All except for F, SM and JM: holotype, male, 6.3 mm (OMNH-Ar-12429); F: paratype, female, 6.2 mm (OMNH-Ar-12433); SM: paratype, small male, 5.1 mm (OMNH-Ar-12430), slender setae omitted; JM: paratype, juvenile male, 3.6 mm (OMNH-Ar-12432), slender setae omitted. Scales: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781803/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
SM-G1), carpus wider than that of 
<typeStatus box="[232,330,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[347,439,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[176,1404,196,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[172,1415,181,1950]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Aora biarticulata sp. nov. Holotype, male, 6.3 mm (OMNH-Ar-12429). Scales: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781801" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781801/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
<figureCitation box="[440,451,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1840,1864]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,900,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-371@3.[151,1436,885,1817]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Aora biarticulata sp. nov. Holotype, male, 6.3 mm (OMNH-Ar-12429). Habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781797" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781797/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">1</figureCitation>
); propodus ca. 0.85 times as long as carpus, palm oblique, defined by long robust seta; dactylus posterior margin with 6 denticles. 
<typeStatus box="[630,731,475,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Paratype</typeStatus>
, juvenile male (OMNH-Ar-12432, 
<quantity box="[1123,1212,475,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
). 
<emphasis box="[1230,1376,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Gnathopod 1</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[194,1392,195,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-26@6.[181,1406,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Aora biarticulata sp. nov. All except for F, SM and JM: holotype, male, 6.3 mm (OMNH-Ar-12429); F: paratype, female, 6.2 mm (OMNH-Ar-12433); SM: paratype, small male, 5.1 mm (OMNH-Ar-12430), slender setae omitted; JM: paratype, juvenile male, 3.6 mm (OMNH-Ar-12432), slender setae omitted. Scales: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781803" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781803/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
JM-G1), merus short, with distal tip reaching half-length of carpus; propodus ca. 1.1 times length of carpus, palm oblique, defined by long robust seta; dactylus posterior margin with 4 denticles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,535,582,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,410,582,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Coloration in life.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="400" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,619,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ariyama &amp; Kohtsuka, 2022" authorityName="Ariyama &amp; Kohtsuka" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,517,619,645]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Aora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biarticulata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,517,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Aora biarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[524,613,619,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[524,613,619,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is characterized by (1) accessory flagellum with 2 articles, (2) weakly setose male gnathopod 1 with rounded coxa, and (3) male gnathopod 2 with setose carpus and propodus (setose only on posterior margin of carpus and both anterior and posterior margins of propodus). There is no other 
<taxonomicName box="[1292,1436,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis box="[1292,1348,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Aora</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
possessing all these characters. Especially in the accessory flagellum, the number of articles varies from 
<quantity box="[1340,1436,727,753]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.143" metricValueMax="1.524" metricValueMin="0.762" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" unit="in" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3 to 6 in</quantity>
the 
<taxonomicName box="[192,335,763,789]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis box="[192,248,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Aora</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
except for this new species (unknown in 
<taxonomicName authority="Myers &amp; Moore, 1983" authorityName="Myers &amp; Moore" authorityYear="1983" box="[796,1219,763,789]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Aora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adpressa">
<emphasis box="[796,959,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Aora adpressa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Myers, A. A. &amp; Moore, P. G." box="[966,1219,763,789]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" pagination="167 - 180" refId="ref9939" refString="Myers, A. A. &amp; Moore, P. G. (1983) The New Zealand and south-east Australian species of Aora Kroyer (Amphipoda, Gammaridea). Records of the Australian Museum, 35, 167 - 180. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0067 - 1975.35.1983.316" type="journal article" year="1983">Myers &amp; Moore, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schellenberg, 1926" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Aora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anomala">
<emphasis box="[1230,1358,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">A. anomala</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schellenberg, A." pageId="7" pageNumber="400" pagination="235 - 414" refId="ref10088" refString="Schellenberg, A. (1926) Die Gammariden der Deutschen Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903. Deutsche Sudpolar Expedition, 18 (Zoologie 10), 235 - 414." type="journal article" year="1926">Schellenberg, 1926</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="K. H. Barnard, 1932" authorityName="K. H. Barnard" authorityYear="1932" box="[364,711,799,825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Aora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gibbula">
<emphasis box="[364,480,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">A. gibbula</emphasis>
K.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnard, K. H." box="[548,711,799,825]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" pagination="1 - 326" refId="ref8867" refString="Barnard, K. H. (1932) Amphipoda. Discovery Reports, 5, 1 - 326, 1 pl. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 27664" type="journal article" year="1932">Barnard, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ariyama &amp; Kohtsuka" authorityYear="2022" box="[828,990,799,825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Aora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biarticulata">
<emphasis box="[828,990,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">A. biarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a 2-articulated accessory flagellum. Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Myers &amp; Moore" authorityYear="1983" box="[263,426,835,861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Aora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adpressa">
<emphasis box="[263,426,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Aora adpressa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the above characters (2) and (3), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Myers &amp; Moore" authorityYear="1983" box="[842,972,835,861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Aora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adpressa">
